  "text": "The combined results presented here and previously [CITATION_1] suggest that, prior to fusion activation, cell surface F protein exists in several forms that are in equilibrium, and the concentration of each form reflects the concentration of surface isomerases (illustrated in the model shown in Fig. 7) . These results, as well as previous results that showed that the binding of thiol-reactive MPB blocked fusion [CITATION_2] , suggest that it is the form containing free thiols that proceeds through the conformational changes, which results in cell-cell fusion (Fig. 7) .",
